# Replace Wake Word with Camera-Based Presence Detection (MediaPipe)

Replace the current "Hey Jarvis" wake word activation with automatic person-presence detection using **MediaPipe Face Detection**. When a person stands in front of the camera for a sustained period (~3 seconds), AIRA activates and speaks the greeting — no voice trigger needed.

## Why MediaPipe Over YOLOv8?

We evaluated five approaches for person presence detection. Here's why MediaPipe wins for a virtual receptionist:

| Approach | New Deps | CPU Speed | Accuracy | Verdict |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **MediaPipe Face Detection** ⭐ | `mediapipe` (~30MB) | **~10-30ms** | 95%+ | **Best fit** — detects faces facing the camera |
| OpenCV Haar Cascades | None | ~5-15ms | 80-85% | Too many false positives/negatives |
| OpenCV DNN (SSD MobileNet) | None + model file | ~30-50ms | ~90% | Good but requires manual model management |
| YOLOv8n (`ultralytics`) | `ultralytics` (~20MB+) | ~50-100ms | 95%+ | **Overkill** — detects 80 COCO classes when we only need faces |
| Reuse DeepFace's SSD | None | ~100-200ms | ~85% | Too slow for a polling loop |

**Key reasons MediaPipe is better than YOLOv8 for this use case:**

1. **Detects what actually matters** — A face *facing the camera*, not just any person. YOLOv8 would trigger on someone walking 20 feet behind the kiosk with their back turned. MediaPipe only fires when someone is **looking at the screen** — exactly when a receptionist should greet them.

2. **3-5× faster on CPU** — 10-30ms vs 50-100ms per frame. This matters because we're running detection in a loop every 1.5 seconds alongside audio processing, VAD, and DeepFace.

3. **Gives face position + size** — The bounding box tells us if the person is "close enough" (large face = standing at the kiosk) vs "far away" (small face = walking past). YOLO gives a person bounding box but can't distinguish someone at the desk from someone across the room as intuitively.

4. **Lighter dependency** — `mediapipe` is a focused package. `ultralytics` pulls in the entire YOLOv8 ecosystem (training, export, tracking) when we only need one inference call.

5. **Built for exactly this** — Google designed MediaPipe Face Detection for real-time face detection on mobile/edge CPUs. A kiosk receptionist is its ideal deployment scenario.

